Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**1 & 2. Intercept back navigation with a confirmation dialog:**

Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and use the `Shell.Current.Navigation` to handle the software back button:

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () =>
            {
                bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                    "Unsaved Changes",
                    "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                    "Discard", "Stay");

                if (leave)
                    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
            });

            return true; // cancel the default navigation
        }

        return base.OnBackButtonPressed(); // allow normal back
    }
}
```

> `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the **hardware/OS back button** (Android). Returning `true` cancels it.

**3. Custom "Cancel" back button in the toolbar:**

Replace Shell's default back button with your own `ToolbarItem` by hiding the built-in one:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{StaticResource CancelBackButton}">

    <ContentPage.Resources>
        <BackButtonBehavior x:Key="CancelBackButton"
                            TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </ContentPage.Resources>
</ContentPage>
```

Or set it inline (more common):

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                        Command="{Binding CancelCommand}"
                        IconOverride="" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

Then in your view model or code-behind:

```csharp
public ICommand CancelCommand => new Command(async () =>
{
    if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!leave) return;
    }

    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
});
```

**Key points:**
- `OnBackButtonPressed` → hardware/swipe back (Android)
- `BackButtonBehavior` with `Command` → toolbar back button (replaces default)
- Both paths should share the same confirmation logic
- `TextOverride="Cancel"` replaces the arrow with text; use `IconOverride` if you also want to remove any icon
